{"session_id": "0cdcba48-6d52-4d05-81b6-47d656101180", "task": "Implement the following plan:\n\n# Plan: Implement Spec 003 \u2014 Smart Hire\n\n## Context\n\nThe current \"Hire Agent\" flow is a manual form (ID, title, department, description, system_prompt). Spec 003 wants a **natural-language-in, hired-agent-out** flow: Chairman describes a need \u2192 system generates 3 candidates \u2192 each runs a standardized test in parallel \u2192 LLM scores results \u2192 best candidate auto-hired. All events stream to Live Log via WebSocket.\n\n## Architecture\n\nThe heavy lifting (LLM candidate generation + LLM scoring) happens server-side. The client just provides a text input + shows progress via Live Log (already wired). We use Claude API (via `@anthropic-ai/sdk`) directly for the meta-prompts (candidate generation + scoring), NOT by spawning `claude` CLI.\n\n## Implementation (3 commits)\n\n### Commit 1: Server \u2014 Smart Hire engine + route\n\n**File: `server/src/lib/SmartHire.ts`** (new)\n\nCore engine with 3 phases:\n\n1. **Generate candidates** \u2014 Call Claude API with the spec's meta-prompt to produce 3 candidate profiles (JSON array with id, title, department, description, reports_to, system_prompt)\n2. **Run interviews** \u2014 For each candidate, spawn `claude --dangerously-skip-permissions -p \"{test_task}\"` in parallel with 60s timeout. Capture stdout as test output. Use standardized test tasks per department (from spec).\n3. **Score & select** \u2014 Call Claude API with a scoring prompt: pass each candidate's profile + test output, ask for 0-10 scores on 4 dimensions (task_completion 40%, output_quality 30%, autonomy 20%, conciseness 10%). Parse scores, compute weighted average, pick winner.\n4. **Hire winner** \u2014 Create agent directory + profile.json + memory.md (reuse existing `POST /api/hire` logic inline).\n5. **Archive results** \u2014 Save full interview record to `archive/interviews/H-{timestamp}.json`.\n\nAll phases broadcast events: `hire:start`, `hire:candidates`, `hire:interview_start`, `hire:interview_done`, `hire:scores`, `hire:complete`, `hire:error`.\n\n**File: `server/src/route", "stage": "apply", "user_decision": "approve", "edit_distance": 1.0, "user_feedback_text": "", "change_type": "docs", "turn_number": 2, "_swechat_pushback": "non_pushback", "_swechat_persona": "mind_changer", "_swechat_mode": "human_only", "_swechat_intent": "create new code", "_swechat_success": "52.0", "_swechat_agent_pct": 0.0}
